com.siperian.sif.message.hm

Class UpdateRelationshipRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.hm.RelationshipRequestBase
        • com.siperian.sif.message.hm.UpdateRelationshipRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataProvider, ModifyRelationshipRequest, Serializable

    public class UpdateRelationshipRequest
extends RelationshipRequestBase
implements DataProvider, ModifyRelationshipRequest
    Update a Relationship between two Entities. The existing relationship record is updated if the Start Date, End Date, or custom columns for the Relationship record are modified. If the update request changes the Hierarchy, Relationship Type, or one or both Entities in the Relationship, the current Relationship record is deleted (see DeleteRelationshipRequest) and a new Relationship record is added (see AddRelationshipRequest). When a new Relationship record is added, the RecordKey returned in the UpdateRelationshipResponse will be different from the one specified in the UpdateRelationshipRequest.

    Use UpdateRelationshipRequest instead of AddRelationshipRequest to add a new Relationship for a Foreign Key Relationship Type because adding that Relationship really involves updating an existing record in the FK Relationship Base Object. For example, if there is a FK Relationship Base Object C_PERSON with the following columns:

    • Rowid Object: Primary Key for the FK Relationship and the Entity.
    • Rowid Company: FK that refers to the records in C_COMPANY Entity Base Object. The value in this column has a non-null when there a HM FK Relationship between C_PERSON and C_COMPANY. The column value is set to null when the Relationship between a Company and a Person is deleted.
    • Any other columns needed for "Person" Entity Type and "Person To Company" FK Relationship Type.

    The Put Package associated with the "Person To Company" FK Relationship Type would have the following columns:

    • Rowid Object (C_PERSON.Rowid_Object): Primary Key for the FK Relationship
    • Rowid BO1 (C_PERSON.Rowid_Object): BO1 in the FK Relationship
    • Rowid BO2 (C_PERSON.Rowid_Company): BO2 in the FK Relationship

    In other words either rowid BO1 or rowid BO2 in the Put Package maps to the Rowid Object column in the Base Object. Updating the FK column (Rowid BO2 / C_PERSON.Rowid_Company in the example) to a non-null value is equivalent to adding a new FK Relationship. Also note that the RecordKey specified in setRecordKey() and setBo1RecordKey() in this example would be the same.

    UpdateRelationshipRequest cannot be used to modify Relationship Type if the old or the new Relationship Type is a FK Relationship Type. To do that, use DeleteRelationshipRequest to delete the old Relationship. Then use UpdateRelationshipRequest if the new Relationship is a FK Relationship Type or AddRelationshipRequest if the new Relationship is not a FK Relationship Type.

    Required Parameters:

    • RelationshipRequestBase.setHmConfigurationUid(String) - UID of the HM Configuration. For details, see RelationshipRequestBase.
    • RelationshipRequestBase.setRelTypeUid(String) - UID of the Relationship Type. The Relationship Type UID and the HM Configuration UID determine the Relationship Base Object. For more information, see RelationshipRequestBase.
    • RelationshipRequestBase.setRecordKey(RecordKey) - Key for the Relationship record to be updated. For details, see RelationshipRequestBase.

    Note:The above three (3) required parameters just identify the Relationship record to be modified. Specifying just these three parameters does not do anything meaningful. Use the other setter methods to update the Relationship record.

    Usage Examples: The following example updates the Relationship record "123". It associates the Relationship with the "Old Data" Hierarchy, sets the End Date, and specifies a "Reason" (a user defined custom column in the Relationship Base Object).

    UpdateRelationshipRequest request = new UpdateRelationshipRequest();
    request.setHmConfigurationUid("HM_CONFIGURATION.Default|Master");
    request.setRelTypeUid("HM_RELATIONSHIP_TYPE.WorksFor");
    request.setRecordKey(RecordKey.rowid("123", "Accounting"));

    request.setHierarchyUid("HM_HIERARCHY.Old Data");
    request.setEndDate(new Date());
    Record rec = new Record();
    rec.setField(new Field("REASON", "Employee left the company"));
    request.setRecord(rec);

    UpdateRelationshipResponse response =
       (UpdateRelationshipResponse) siperianClient.process(request);

    // Log the information in the response.
    RecordKey key = response.getRecordKey();
    log.info("Updated Relationship record: " + key.getRowid());

    See Also:
